>
  <main id="main"><header class="page-hero page-hero--letterbox"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / <a href="fellowships.html">Fellowships</a> / International Graduates</div><span class="kicker">International Graduate Fellows</span><h1>Global knowledge in service to public missions</h1><p>International Graduate Fellows bring academic achievement, field alignment, perspective, and public purpose to American institutions.</p></div></header><nav class="anchor-nav anchor-nav--index" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#overview"><span>01</span>Overview</a><a href="#process"><span>02</span>How it works</a><a href="#focus"><span>03</span>Areas of focus</a><a href="#principles"><span>04</span>Principles</a><a href="#next"><span>05</span>Next steps</a></div></nav><section class="section letter-opening" id="overview"><div class="container"><div class="letter-meta"><span>US Fellows</span><strong>Service memorandum</strong><small>Subject / Global perspective, field-aligned contribution</small></div><div class="letter-copy"><div class="prose"><span class="eyebrow">The fellowship pathway</span><h2>Global perspective, field-aligned contribution</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>International graduates bring academic knowledge, cultural perspective, and connections across institutions and countries to American public-interest work.</p><p>Appointments are selected on merit and mission fit. They must remain grounded in a qualified host, clear responsibilities, and any independent legal or institutional requirements that apply.</p><p>Academic alignment establishes the point of entry; responsible participation defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div></div></div></section><section class="section process-quadrants" id="process"><div class="container"><div class="process-quadrants__heading"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">From intent to practice</span><h2>From interest to appointment</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Appointments are shaped deliberately so that recognition, institutional affiliation, and useful work reinforce one another.</p></div><p class="process-pull">Academic alignment establishes the point of entry; responsible participation defines what should remain after the immediate work is complete.</p></div><div class="process-quadrants__grid"><article class="step"><h3>Express interest</h3><p>Describe your record, field, mission interests, and the contribution you are ready to make. Here, attend to academic alignment: Connect advanced study to research, analysis, education, innovation, or other substantive field work.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Establish fit</h3><p>Consider merit, readiness, mission alignment, and the setting in which the work can succeed. Here, attend to institutional contribution: Address a real need with outputs and responsibilities appropriate to the Fellow&#x27;s preparation.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Define the appointment</h3><p>Confirm scope, host support, responsibilities, intended benefit, and a practical working cadence. Here, attend to cross-cultural insight: Strengthen collaboration and understanding without reducing a Fellow to nationality or background.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>Serve and reflect</h3><p>Complete the work with rigor, participate in Society life, and share transferable learning. Here, attend to responsible participation: Keep fellowship selection distinct from immigration, employment, licensing, or academic authorization decisions.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section" id="focus"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">The fellowship pathway</span><h2>What this form of fellowship brings together</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>International graduates bring academic knowledge, cultural perspective, and connections across institutions and countries to American public-interest work.</p></div><div class="focus-table"><article class="dimension-card"><span>01</span><LegacyIcon name="compass" /><h3>Academic alignment</h3><p>Connect advanced study to research, analysis, education, innovation, or other substantive field work.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>02</span><LegacyIcon name="institution" /><h3>Institutional contribution</h3><p>Address a real need with outputs and responsibilities appropriate to the Fellow&#x27;s preparation.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>03</span><LegacyIcon name="lightbulb-o" /><h3>Cross-cultural insight</h3><p>Strengthen collaboration and understanding without reducing a Fellow to nationality or background.</p></article><article class="dimension-card"><span>04</span><LegacyIcon name="handshake-o" /><h3>Responsible participation</h3><p>Keep fellowship selection distinct from immigration, employment, licensing, or academic authorization decisions.</p></article></div></div></section><section class="section principle-annotations" id="principles"><div class="container"><aside><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Appointment standard</span><h2>Commitments behind a credible fellowship</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>A strong appointment aligns the Fellow, the institution, and the public value of the work.</p></div></aside><div class="principle-annotations__list"><article class="principle-row"><span>01</span><div><h3>Field alignment</h3><p>A Fellow&#x27;s knowledge and capabilities should be relevant to the work the appointment requires.</p></div></article><article class="principle-row"><span>02</span><div><h3>Institutional fit</h3><p>The host setting should make the contribution feasible, responsible, and useful.</p></div></article><article class="principle-row"><span>03</span><div><h3>Public value</h3><p>The appointment should create benefit beyond private career advancement or organizational convenience.</p></div></article></div></div></section><section class="section close-ledger" id="next"><div class="container"><span class="close-ledger__index" aria-hidden="true">05</span><div><div><h2>Move from interest toward appointment</h2><p>Begin with academic alignment, then define a contribution your capabilities or institution can support.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="apply.html">Become a Fellow</a><a class="button button--outline" href="fellowship-programs.html">View programs</a></div></div><aside class="related-panel"><span class="eyebrow">Continue exploring</span><h3>Related pathways</h3><ul class="related-list"><li><a href="fellowship-programs.html">Fellowship programs</a></li><li><a href="selection-criteria.html">Selection criteria</a></li><li><a href="fellow-benefits.html">The Fellow experience</a></li></ul></aside></div></section></main>

</BaseLayout>
